author: Jennifer ruby
title: Celebrity Big Brother 2017: Jedward make their return to the house
text:
Saturday 7 January 2017 07:19 BST They're back: Jedward enter the Celebrity Big Brother house at Elstree Studios PA 
Former X Factor stars Jedward have entered the Celebrity Big Brother house, six years after their first stint in the compound. 
The Irish singers, who first found fame when they came sixth on The X Factor in 2009, took part in the eighth series of the reality show in 2011 and have represented Ireland in the Eurovision Song Contest. 
Jonathan Cheban was expected to also be a new arrivals but is rumoured to have fallen out with producers ahead of his arrival. 
Jedward - identical 25-year-old twins Edward and John Grimes - were previously holed up in the house with Kerry Katona and American Pie star Tara Reid, who later got them a cameo in her film Sharknado 3: Oh Hell No! 
Ahead of entering the house for the second time, the duo told host Emma Willis it was "an honour" to return to the show. 
"It's going to be like a great sequel. We're so excited." 
They added: "I think we'll get on with everybody, I think everybody needs Jedward the most. Victory: Will Jedward win this year's Celebrity Big Brother? (Stefan Rousseau/PA Wire) 
Asked if they will bring a bit of naughtiness into the house, the duo said: "Of course that's us. That's part of us." 
The two waltzed into the house in a cloud of smoke and dressed as astronauts before performing for their fellow housemates. Celebrity Big Brother 2017: most shocking moments so far 
They entered the house just moments after it was revealed actor James Cosmo would be automatically facing the first live eviction. 
In true Big Brother style, the series had kicked off with a rather cruel twist, with the ‘All Stars’ given the power to ‘edit out’ fellow housemates. 
Stacy Francis, Cosmo and Brandon Block were the first to be ‘edited out’, which meant that they had to wear beige tracksuits and were excluded from any house activities. 
Games Of Thrones star Cosmo was not selected by All Star celebrities Jamie O'Hara and Angie Best who had the chance to save the "edited out" housemates. 
It was also revealed that the edited out celebrities, also including singer Ray J Norwood and model Bianca Gascoigne, will not be allowed to nominate for the first eviction. 
A major row erupted between housemates Heidi Pratt and Austin Armacost in scenes aired on Friday’s show. 
Armacost was summoned to the diary room after losing his rag with the reality star over stolen bottles of water. Celebrity Big Brother Launch 2017 - In pictures Celebrity Big Brother Launch 2017 - In pictures 1/17
